has tag "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
=======================================================

NAME
----

has tag - Check if the current post has any of the given tags. The given tags are

SYNOPSIS
--------

Check if the current post has any of the given tags. The given tags are
checked against the post's tags' term\_ids, names and slugs. Tags given
as integers will only be checked against the post's tags' term\_ids.

\
 If no tags are given, determines if post has any tags.

USAGE
-----

` <?php has_tag( $tag, $post ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$tag` 
:   ([*mixed*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Mixed "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The tag name, term\_id or slug. Also accepts an array
    of tag names, term ids and slugs
    Default: *None*

 `$post` 
:   ([*object*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Object "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Post to check instead of the current post.
    Default: Current post

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `(boolean)` 
:   True if the current post has any of the the given tags (or any tag,
    if no tag specified), false otherwise.

CHANGELOG
---------

Since: 2.6.0

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`has_tag()` is located in `wp-includes/category-template.php`.

